 more than their fair share of life times. In its own way; even tho it may reveal a bit too much or give away little secrets, writing in the Literaries, might allow some of us to build confidence in our characters, and bring that with us on Friday night. maybe it will give us a little more to bring into the &quot;Live Action&quot; portion of our game on friday night, and make the interactions that much richer, and more enjoyable. In a way, maybe the confidence of our character, will help us, to be more confident as we represent that character. Actors speak of &quot;Motivation&quot; are we not then actors, seeking motivations for the characters we portrait every friday night? Yet unlike actors who protrait characters in a movie, we protrait them on the streets, session after session, for years sometimes. I am a writer, a set designer, a stage combat coreographer, a sound and lighting technitian, a carpenter and electrician, and until I became a live-action RolePlayer, I had never acted. Now, after writing the stories in my head about fantastical vampires onto paper, and occasionaly into electronic forums, and attempting to assume that role on the streets,I think I may now begin to add &quot;Actor&quot; to my list of accomplishments. Perhaps writing in a literary forum is not technically &quot;LiveAction&quot; roleplaying, but for many of us, it is this forum, that gives Life to that which we attempt to portrait.<br>
Always in deepest regards for the opinions of others,<br>
Scott~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keiranblack>Keiran Black</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Clan Gangrel</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/4/03 4:31:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Literary posts</span><hr size=1> Ok, time for one of the actors to chime in.<br>
<br>
I enjoy the literary posts simply because they tend to flush out a character that might not get the chance to grow due to the 3-4 hours a week we spend in character.  It's our opportunity to create subtlety, nuance, and fire in our character as well as entertain the other players and Staff during the wekk.  It is yet another creative outlet in the WoD.  Being told a blanket statement about a character is one thing but getting to read a piece of their history is another.  I can explain that my character is a Hunter all day long...but it adds to the presence of the character if the players OOC have some sort of reference.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion...<br>
<br>
I enjoy the Literary posts and plan to continue writing once auditions are done.<br>
<br>
~Mike <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bscbnforum58570.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hart@scbnforum58570>Hart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF9300>(2/12/03 11:57:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lit posts vs larp</span><hr size=1> To sum up<br>
Literary posts should not be a substitution for good rollplaying.<br>
If you don't get into actually playing your character you will miss out, and miss the point.<br>
The lits are just suplementary.<br>
They are cool, and fun, and important, but not a replacement for playing the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/prefabs/ez/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fscbnforum58570frm16.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="scbnforum58570frm12">Blackjack's Message Board <option value="scbnforum58570frm21">The Barrens<option value="scbnforum58570frm23">Domain Status<option value="scbnforum58570frm18">The Santa Carla Tribune<option value="scbnforum58570frm19">Literary<option value="scbnforum58570frm16">Players Forum<option value="scbnforum58570frm17">Storyteller and Narrator Announcements</select></td><td><input type=submit value="Go" cl